{"parse":{"title":"Media ritual","pageid":49552930,"revid":712909817,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Media ritual</b> is a term used to describe a <a href=\"/wiki/Theory\" title=\"Theory\">theoretical</a> approach in the field of <a href=\"/wiki/Media_studies\" title=\"Media studies\">media</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Communication_studies\" title=\"Communication studies\">communication</a> studies, which borrows thematically from the field of <a href=\"/wiki/Anthropology\" title=\"Anthropology\">anthropology</a>. The theory is based upon <a href=\"/wiki/James_W._Carey\" title=\"James W. Carey\">Carey</a>'s 'ritual view of communication' in which he asserts that \"news reading, and writing, is a ritual act and moreover a dramatic one<b>.</b>\" (Carey, 1989<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>). This 'ritual' view of communication is in contrast to his 'transmission' view of communication. Media ritual theory has been elaborated in recent years, popularised in particular by Nick Couldry (e.g. Couldry, 2003<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>).\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Media_ritual&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Carey, James W. (1989-01-01). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=AcSufbsE7TwC\"><i>Communication as Culture: Essays on Media and Society</i></a>. Psychology Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780415907255\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780415907255\">9780415907255</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Communication+as+Culture%3A+Essays+on+Media+and+Society&amp;rft.pub=Psychology+Press&amp;rft.date=1989-01-01&amp;rft.isbn=9780415907255&amp;rft.aulast=Carey&amp;rft.aufirst=James+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DAcSufbsE7TwC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMedia+ritual\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Couldry, Nick (2003-01-01). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=RslZmAEACAAJ\"><i>Media Rituals: A Critical Approach</i></a>. Routledge. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780415270144\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780415270144\">9780415270144</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Media+Rituals%3A+A+Critical+Approach&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=2003-01-01&amp;rft.isbn=9780415270144&amp;rft.aulast=Couldry&amp;rft.aufirst=Nick&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DRslZmAEACAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMedia+ritual\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Anthropostub.png\" class=\"image\